        <item>
          <title>Salesforce Expands AI Model Sharing with Google, Bets Big on Agentic AI</title>
          <description><![CDATA[Salesforce and Google Cloud have announced a major expansion of their strategic partnership, involving the sharing of cloud and AI resources. Central to this deal is the ability for Salesforce customers to build AI agents using Google's Gemini models and deploy Salesforce on Google Cloud. The emergence of agentic AI, estimated to be worth $2 trillion, has significant implications for businesses looking to transform with AI.]]></description>
          <guid>https://majordigest.com/tech/2025/02/25/salesforce-and-google-cloud-sign-multi-billion-dollar-software-deal-which-could-affect-how-you-use-ai-at-work/</guid>
